summary: Going to the gym alone via /r/Fitness
title: Going to the gym alone via /r/Fitness
body:
Hello

So I fell out with my gym buddy (wants me to pay for petrol for going gym, fair enough but I know this guy is gonna just make me pay for everything), and I’m not sure if I’m even going to bother going to the gym alone.

I’ve made a bit of progress with my short time at the gym, but I still find I need spotting constantly on low weights, especially benching and dumbbells.

I just don’t know if I can see myself going to the gym alone, so thought I’d see if anyone here can help motivate me to do this.



Submitted March 01, 2019 at 05:08AM by chimingbarframe

title: Still high Triglycerides!?? via /r/Fitness
body:
Background: male 16 5’10” 152 lbs That would make my BMI 21.8 and my Height/Waist ratio 42.86%

I’ve been losing weight since July and have successfully lost 50 lbs. I have cut out all processed food and all added sugars. I only drink water, black coffee, and tea. The only fats I eat are nuts and avocado, and the occasional dollop of olive oil in recipes. I obviously don’t drink (since that’s a factor)

I exercise 5x a week. 20-30 minute runs during the school week, and one long run ~7 miles or 90 minutes on Saturday. I always do a little bodyweight exercise too.

With all that… why are my triglycerides still high???? i feel like I’ve done everything right.



Submitted March 01, 2019 at 05:35AM by sdgyft
via reddit https://ift.tt/2XvGeiY

summary: Don’t forget to leave your desk and move around regularly - lack of movement or long sitting harm the spine, as you, a human,...
question: Don’t forget to leave your desk and move around regularly - lack of movement or long sitting harm the spine, as you, a human, probably get painfully reminded of.
answer:
Oh, trust me, I shouldn’t need to be reminded, but for some reason once I get focused on something, I zone out everything else. And my back takes great exception to it, but it has to wait until I have enough brain space to process pain, before it can punish me.

But, thanks for the reminder. I’ll take a break now.

summary: NGS Data Analysis Market: Clinical Diagnosis and Agricultural Research to Expand Demands
title: NGS Data Analysis Market: Clinical Diagnosis and Agricultural Research to Expand Demands
body:
Backed by a rather extended disease burden owing to a host of contributing factors such as changing lifestyle, pollution, and genetic factors, advancements in research and developments have remained integral across healthcare, pharmaceutical, and bioinformatics, not excluding agricultural research which too remains crucial for superlative crop yield. Vast sequential data upsurge on the back of meticulous research activities have instigated adoption of sophisticated data analysis system to intricately infer research outcome and analyze large data volume. Next Generation Sequencing (NGS), a novelty in data analysis algorithm has demonstrated promising outcome in research and development endeavors, thereby the technology has fast substituted conventional sequencing formats such as Capillary Electrophoresis to offset functional bottlenecks and latency associated with workflow configuration.

Research and development pertaining drug discovery, agricultural research in quest for resilient crop varieties, and novel therapeutics for life-threating maladies, continues to remain a cost intensive affair, often witnessing discontinuation and abortion on the back of resource constraints. Factors as such have therefore prompted adoption of advanced analytics tools which can accentuate research, thus augmenting breakthroughs in the interest of common welfare. NGS as an evolved sequencing technology enables gene sequencing of high throughput data volume with optimum cost efficiency. The attribute has catapulted disease therapeutics of chronic ailments such as cancer, besides manifesting tangible innovations in rare disease therapeutic management.

Exome Sequencing to Remain Most Sought After Service of NGS Data Analysis in Clinical Oncology

Cancer continues to baffle and intimidate humankind with frequent instances and limited disease management success. According to estimations cited by Cancer Research UK, the global cancer burden is likely to increase by 62% for the period 2018-2040. Under these circumstances, healthcare and diagnostics heavily rely on novel technologies to attain actionable insights in comprehending rare disease symptoms, triggers, and subsequent prognosis.

NGS has been widely accepted as an efficient tool for predicting early signs and symptoms of cancers well ahead, even before the first symptoms are actually evident. Limitations associated with other precedent technologies such as Sanger sequencing have been eliminated significantly with the embracement of NGS Data Analysis Market. It aids in mutation identification and subsequent sequencing analysis of the genome as a whole. Besides genome sequencing, subject experts also rely upon exome and transcriptome sequencing. The effectiveness of NGS in clinical oncology has significantly aided physicians in suggesting apt disease management post a complete genomic profile test. However, backed by an overwhelming data cluster and associated data complexity pertaining validation methods for accurate mutation identification, providers are keen on introducing new and advanced tools and techniques that aids bioinformatics, hence the need for apt analysis remains integral.  Besides offering useful assistance in cancer pre-diagnostics, the technique has also left a mark in other rare disease therapeutics such as Alzheimer’s and even in infectious disease management.

Sequencing by synthesis (SBS) Reigns Supreme as Most Accurate Data Analysis Technique

Pioneered by scientist duo from University of Cambridge, the sequencing -by-synthesis technology, often abbreviated as SBS technique has witnessed enormous developmental milestones under Illumina that purchased all commercial rights of SBS a decade back. The technique bears substantial resemblance with the first sequencing platform, Sanger, however, owing to several improvements and technological advancements, SBS reigns as the most preferred NGS technology that alone contributes to staggering data sequencing volume globally.

Its uniquely designed sequencing approach, based on reversible dye-terminators enables single base identification when introduced to DNA strands, also ensuring error-free data for a whole gamut of applications, unlike its predecessor, Sanger. Owing to its evolved technological expertise, SBS finds ample applications across a series of sequencing applications comprising whole-genome sequencing, transcriptomics, metagenomics, and RNA discovery amongst several others.

New Genome Wide Next Generation Sequencing Improves Prenatal Genetic Diagnosis

To further expand boundaries, research institutes, hospitals, and academic institutions are awaiting process improvisation to comply with automated operations and cloud computing structure. Stakeholders therefore are akin on offering superlative sequencing platforms. Emergence of genome-wide, next generation sequencing that enables simultaneous detection of multiple monogenic disorders, aneuploidies, and translocations within a single biopsy test has been acknowledge as a class apart sequencing technique anticipated to revolutionize prenatal genetic diagnosis. This new addition offers promising outcome in terms of short turnaround times as well as data precision allowing well-informed decisions for embryo selection to ensue healthy pregnancy, thereby striking off chances of miscarriages in older women.

Need specific, automated tool design to ease out data integration and workflow configuration have paved way for real-time-analysis software that is designed to offer ample quality checks pertaining DNA and RNA strands. Further, development of ideal push-button apps overlooking DNA sequence alignment and data visualization pertaining diverse RNA sequencing experiments are further expected to transform the face of analytical tools, thereby elevating next generation sequencing gamut.

summary: Rare set of semi-identical twins identified in Australia
title: Rare set of semi-identical twins identified in Australia
body:
A pair of Australian twins had researchers scratching their heads when it was discovered they were neither identical nor fraternal, but semi-identical siblings.

Read more from CTV Health News https://www.ctvnews.ca/sci-tech/rare-set-of-semi-identical-twins-identified-in-australia-1.4316382
